-- Chevron Natural Gas Pipeline Leaks in Gulf of Mexico: NRC Report
-- B y   R e b e c c a   P e n t y
-- 2013-09-01T19:55:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-01/chevron-natural-gas-pipeline-leaks-in-gulf-of-mexico-nrc-report.html
Chevron Corp. (CVX)  leaked an unknown
quantity of natural gas from a pipeline in the Gulf of Mexico
near Pascagoula, Mississippi, according to a report filed Aug.
30 with the U.S. National Response Center.  An investigation was under way by a dive team according to
the  report , filed at 5:24 p.m. local time on Aug. 30.  Bloomberg News couldn’t immediately verify the information
in the filing was accurate.  Kurt Glaubitz , a Chevron spokesman, didn’t immediately
respond to an e-mail inquiry today, outside of normal business
hours.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rebecca Penty in Calgary at 
 rpenty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
